<subSubSection id="04E2D49BFFC3FFD9D7D5292CB5194B26" pageId="8" pageNumber="423" type="description">
<paragraph id="4C478710FFC3FFD9D7D5292CB6C14C12" blockId="8.[178,1086,541,592]" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">
E t y m o l o g y: This species is dedicated to Heinrich Meybohm (Grosshansdorf), who collected all the 
<typeStatus id="934339B2FFC3FFD9D63E2909B6BF4C12" box="[345,389,571,592]" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">type</typeStatus>
specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C478710FFC3FFD9D7D52952B6DC4C8F" blockId="8.[178,1086,608,717]" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size variable; body length 1.8-2.7 mm; length of forebody 0.8-1.1 mm. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="D4C39B95FFC3FFD9D6E7294FB6F54CD1" box="[384,463,637,659]" captionStart="Figs 11-20" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1488,1508]" captionTargetBox="[179,1066,213,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[178,1070,212,1475]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 11-20: Leptusa meybohmi nov.sp. (11-16) and L. hummleriana BERNHAUER (17-20; 17: paralectotype of L. hummleriana; 18: paralectotype of L. sardoa from Dorgali; 19: male from Catena del Márghine; 20: male from Monte Arci): (11) habitus; (12) forebody; (13) male tergite VIII; (14) male sternite VIII; (15-20) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 11: 1.0 mm; 12: 0.5 mm; 13-14: 0.2 mm; 15-20: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4526296" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4526296/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
. Coloration: body reddish to dark-reddish, with abdominal segment VI and sometimes also the anterior portion of segment VII infuscate; legs and antennae yellowish-red to red.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C478710FFC3FFD9D7D529EFB4A04D6F" blockId="8.[178,1086,733,813]" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">
Head (
<figureCitation id="D4C39B95FFC3FFD9D79C29EFB6704CB1" box="[251,330,733,755]" captionStart="Figs 11-20" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1488,1508]" captionTargetBox="[179,1066,213,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[178,1070,212,1475]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 11-20: Leptusa meybohmi nov.sp. (11-16) and L. hummleriana BERNHAUER (17-20; 17: paralectotype of L. hummleriana; 18: paralectotype of L. sardoa from Dorgali; 19: male from Catena del Márghine; 20: male from Monte Arci): (11) habitus; (12) forebody; (13) male tergite VIII; (14) male sternite VIII; (15-20) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 11: 1.0 mm; 12: 0.5 mm; 13-14: 0.2 mm; 15-20: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4526296" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4526296/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) approximately as broad as long; punctation fine, shallow, and rather sparse, barely noticeable in the pronounced microreticulation. Eyes approximately half as long as postocular region and composed of 10-15 rather large ommatidia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C478710FFC3FFD9D7D5280FB57F4DCF" blockId="8.[178,1086,828,909]" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="D4C39B95FFC3FFD9D640280EB6494D10" box="[295,371,828,850]" captionStart="Figs 11-20" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1488,1508]" captionTargetBox="[179,1066,213,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[178,1070,212,1475]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 11-20: Leptusa meybohmi nov.sp. (11-16) and L. hummleriana BERNHAUER (17-20; 17: paralectotype of L. hummleriana; 18: paralectotype of L. sardoa from Dorgali; 19: male from Catena del Márghine; 20: male from Monte Arci): (11) habitus; (12) forebody; (13) male tergite VIII; (14) male sternite VIII; (15-20) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 11: 1.0 mm; 12: 0.5 mm; 13-14: 0.2 mm; 15-20: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4526296" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4526296/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) 1.15-1.20 times as broad as long and approximately 1.15 times as broad as head; posterior angles very weakly marked, nearly obsolete; punctation and microsculpture similar to those of head.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C478710FFC3FFD9D7D528AEB50C4A48" blockId="8.[178,1086,924,1034]" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="D4C39B95FFC3FFD9D66528AEB6754DF0" box="[258,335,924,946]" captionStart="Figs 11-20" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1488,1508]" captionTargetBox="[179,1066,213,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[178,1070,212,1475]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 11-20: Leptusa meybohmi nov.sp. (11-16) and L. hummleriana BERNHAUER (17-20; 17: paralectotype of L. hummleriana; 18: paralectotype of L. sardoa from Dorgali; 19: male from Catena del Márghine; 20: male from Monte Arci): (11) habitus; (12) forebody; (13) male tergite VIII; (14) male sternite VIII; (15-20) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 11: 1.0 mm; 12: 0.5 mm; 13-14: 0.2 mm; 15-20: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4526296" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4526296/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) approximately 0.65 times as long as pronotum; humeral angles rather marked; lateral margins often more or less distinctly elevated and more or less sharply marked, particularly near the humeral angles; disc with pronounced microreticulation and matt. Hind wings completely reduced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C478710FFC3FFD9D7D52F2BB6754AC5" blockId="8.[178,1086,1049,1159]" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Abdomen distinctly broader than elytra; punctation fine, moderately sparse on anterior tergites, gradually decreasing in density posteriad, and sparse on posterior tergites; tergite VII and VIII with sexual dimorphism; posterior margin of tergite VII without palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C478710FFC3FFD9D7D52FA7B4964B60" blockId="8.[178,1086,1173,1314]" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">
6: tergite VII with glossy oblong median tubercle posteriorly; tergite VIII (
<figureCitation id="D4C39B95FFC3FFD9D4DF2FA5B3384AEF" box="[952,1026,1175,1197]" captionStart="Figs 11-20" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1488,1508]" captionTargetBox="[179,1066,213,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[178,1070,212,1475]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 11-20: Leptusa meybohmi nov.sp. (11-16) and L. hummleriana BERNHAUER (17-20; 17: paralectotype of L. hummleriana; 18: paralectotype of L. sardoa from Dorgali; 19: male from Catena del Márghine; 20: male from Monte Arci): (11) habitus; (12) forebody; (13) male tergite VIII; (14) male sternite VIII; (15-20) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 11: 1.0 mm; 12: 0.5 mm; 13-14: 0.2 mm; 15-20: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4526296" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4526296/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) with small oblong median tubercle (sometimes missing particularly in smaller males), posterior margin weakly concave in the middle and serrate; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="D4C39B95FFC3FFD9D4822FE3B30F4AA5" box="[997,1077,1233,1255]" captionStart="Figs 11-20" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1488,1508]" captionTargetBox="[179,1066,213,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[178,1070,212,1475]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 11-20: Leptusa meybohmi nov.sp. (11-16) and L. hummleriana BERNHAUER (17-20; 17: paralectotype of L. hummleriana; 18: paralectotype of L. sardoa from Dorgali; 19: male from Catena del Márghine; 20: male from Monte Arci): (11) habitus; (12) forebody; (13) male tergite VIII; (14) male sternite VIII; (15-20) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 11: 1.0 mm; 12: 0.5 mm; 13-14: 0.2 mm; 15-20: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4526296" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4526296/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
) transverse, posterior margin distinctly produced in the middle; median lobe of aedeagus 0.23-0.24 mm long, shaped as in 
<figureCitation id="D4C39B95FFC3FFD9D5642E3EB5484B60" box="[515,626,1292,1314]" captionStart="Figs 11-20" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1488,1508]" captionTargetBox="[179,1066,213,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[178,1070,212,1475]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 11-20: Leptusa meybohmi nov.sp. (11-16) and L. hummleriana BERNHAUER (17-20; 17: paralectotype of L. hummleriana; 18: paralectotype of L. sardoa from Dorgali; 19: male from Catena del Márghine; 20: male from Monte Arci): (11) habitus; (12) forebody; (13) male tergite VIII; (14) male sternite VIII; (15-20) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 11: 1.0 mm; 12: 0.5 mm; 13-14: 0.2 mm; 15-20: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4526296" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4526296/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Figs 15-16</figureCitation>
; apical lobe of paramere short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4C478710FFC3FFD9D7D52E07B5194B26" blockId="8.[178,1085,1329,1380]" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">
<specimenCount id="5AFE4C99FFC3FFD9D7D52E07B7FD4B0E" box="[178,199,1333,1356]" pageId="8" pageNumber="423" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: posterior margin of tergite VIII not serrate; sternite VIII with convex posterior margin; spermatheca not distinctive.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="04E2D49BFFC3FFDBD7D52E41B6964F24" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="425" pageId="8" pageNumber="423" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4C478710FFC3FFDBD7D52E41B6964F24" blockId="8.[178,1086,1395,1593]" lastBlockId="10.[178,1085,218,358]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="425" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">
C o m p a r a t i v e n o t e s: Three species of endemic 
<taxonomicName id="8BF8FC93FFC3FFD9D47C2E46B33E4BC8" authority="KRAATZ 1856" authorityName="KRAATZ" authorityYear="1856" box="[795,1028,1396,1418]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC3FFD9D47C2E46B4514BCB" box="[795,875,1396,1417]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Leptusa</emphasis>
KRAATZ 1856
</taxonomicName>
were previously known from 
<collectingRegion id="8E3C49F2FFC3FFD9D6DB2EA3B52E4BE5" box="[444,532,1425,1447]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
: 
<taxonomicName id="8BF8FC93FFC3FFD9D5412EA0B4434BE5" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" box="[550,889,1425,1447]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hummleriana" subGenus="Adexiopisalia">
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC3FFD9D5412EA0B5014BE5" box="[550,571,1426,1447]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC3FFD9D5362EA3B5E64BE5" box="[593,732,1425,1447]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Adexiopisalia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC3FFD9D5952EA3B4434BE5" box="[754,889,1425,1447]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">hummleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8BF8FC93FFC3FFD9D4EA2EA0B6224B86" authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1932" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcicollis" subGenus="Lasiopisalia">
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC3FFD9D4EA2EA0B4984BE5" box="[909,930,1426,1447]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC3FFD9D4D02EA3B30E4BE5" box="[951,1076,1425,1447]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">Lasiopisalia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC3FFD9D7D52E9CB6224B86" box="[178,280,1454,1476]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">sulcicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC3FFD9D63E2E9DB6544B86" box="[345,366,1455,1476]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">L.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC3FFD9D6E72E9DB6AF4B86" box="[384,405,1455,1476]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">L.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC3FFD9D6CF2E9CB53B4B86" box="[424,513,1454,1476]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">brigantii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2869FAE1FFC3FFD9D56C2E9DB5B84B86" author="PACE R" box="[523,642,1454,1476]" pageId="8" pageNumber="423" pagination="1978 - 1979" refId="ref7997" refString="PACE R. (1979): Leptusa KR. nuove o poco note del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova (Coleoptera Staphylinidae). - Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; Giacomo Doria &quot; 82 [1978 - 1979]: 295 - 322." type="journal article" year="1979">PACE 1979</bibRefCitation>
. The new species is readily distinguished from the latter two by the presence of median keels on the male tergites VII and VIII and by the different shapes of the median lobe and of the internal structures of the aedeagus. In external and the sexual characters, it is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8BF8FC93FFC3FFD9D4652D35B49E485E" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" box="[770,932,1542,1564]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hummleriana">
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC3FFD9D4652D35B49E485E" box="[770,932,1542,1564]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">L. hummleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by darker coloration (
<taxonomicName id="8BF8FC93FFC3FFD9D6B02D16B543487B" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" box="[471,633,1571,1593]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="423" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hummleriana">
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC3FFD9D6B02D16B543487B" box="[471,633,1571,1593]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="423">L. hummleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: body yellowish-red to pale-reddish), by the absence of a distinct sexual dimorphism of the elytra (
<taxonomicName id="8BF8FC93FFC1FFDBD5832BE9B4BD4EB2" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" box="[740,903,218,240]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hummleriana">
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC1FFDBD5832BE9B4BD4EB2" box="[740,903,218,240]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="425">L. hummleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: male elytra with granulose punctation and usually with pair of elevations anteriorly), and by the slightly smaller and differently shaped median lobe of the aedeagus. For illustrations of 
<taxonomicName id="8BF8FC93FFC1FFDBD34F2A24B6234F0A" authorityName="BERNHAUER" authorityYear="1932" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcicollis">
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC1FFDBD34F2A24B6234F0A" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="425">L. sulcicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC1FFDBD63C2A01B6E24F0A" box="[347,472,306,328]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="425">L. brigantii</emphasis>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="2869FAE1FFC1FFDBD5712A01B5984F0A" author="PACE R" box="[534,674,306,328]" pageId="10" pageNumber="425" pagination="1 - 307" refId="ref8085" refString="PACE R. (1989): Monografia del genere Leptusa KRAATZ (Coleoptera Staphylinidae). - Memorie del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona (II a Serie), Sezione Scienze della Vita (A: Biologica) 8: 1 - 307." type="journal article" year="1989">PACE (1989)</bibRefCitation>
; the aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName id="8BF8FC93FFC1FFDBD4142A01B3274F0A" authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1935" box="[883,1053,306,328]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hummleriana">
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC1FFDBD4142A01B3274F0A" box="[883,1053,306,328]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="425">L. hummleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="D4C39B95FFC1FFDBD65F2A62B6964F24" box="[312,428,336,358]" captionStart="Figs 11-20" captionStartId="9.[178,218,1488,1508]" captionTargetBox="[179,1066,213,1475]" captionTargetId="figure-1@9.[178,1070,212,1475]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 11-20: Leptusa meybohmi nov.sp. (11-16) and L. hummleriana BERNHAUER (17-20; 17: paralectotype of L. hummleriana; 18: paralectotype of L. sardoa from Dorgali; 19: male from Catena del Márghine; 20: male from Monte Arci): (11) habitus; (12) forebody; (13) male tergite VIII; (14) male sternite VIII; (15-20) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 11: 1.0 mm; 12: 0.5 mm; 13-14: 0.2 mm; 15-20: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4526296" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4526296/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="425">Figs 17-20.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
