<subSubSection id="04E2D49BFFC1FFDBD7D52A44B5944C42" pageId="10" pageNumber="425" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4C478710FFC1FFDBD7D52A44B5944C42" blockId="10.[178,1085,373,512]" pageId="10" pageNumber="425">
D i s t r i b u t i o n a n d n a t u r a l h i s t o r y 
<taxonomicName id="8BF8FC93FFC1FFDBD4652A44B4F84FC9" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2014" box="[770,962,373,395]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Leptusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="425" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meybohmi">
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC1FFDBD4652A44B4F84FC9" box="[770,962,373,395]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="425">Leptusa meybohmi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known only from two localities near Lanusei in the northeast of 
<collectingRegion id="8E3C49F2FFC1FFDBD4232AA0B4A64FEA" box="[836,924,402,424]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="10" pageNumber="425">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
. The specimens were sifted from leaf litter in an oak forest and under bushes and 
<emphasis id="7E8C5B02FFC1FFDBD42F2A82B4F24F87" box="[840,968,431,453]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="425">Quercus ilex</emphasis>
at altitudes of 900 and 
<quantity id="8B002AF5FFC1FFDBD64E2AFFB6564FA0" box="[297,364,461,483]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="10" pageNumber="425" unit="m" value="340.0">340 m</quantity>
, respectively (MEYBOHM pers. comm.). The low altitudes suggest that the species may be more widespread in the island.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
